-- Greece's National Bank posts 2013 profit, provisions ease
-- 
-- Thu Mar 20, 2014 11:39AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, March 20 (Reuters) - National Bank (NBG) <NBGr.AT>, Greece's largest lender by assets, on Thursday reported a profit for 2013, helped by reduced funding costs, its Turkish unit Finansbank and lower bad-loan provisions as the pace of new credit impairments slowed.

